  <h2>Quick Install</h2>
  <pre><code># Homebrew (macOS / Linux)
brew tap yvgude/lean-ctx && brew install lean-ctx

# Arch Linux (AUR)
yay -S lean-ctx          # builds from source
yay -S lean-ctx-bin      # pre-built binary

# Windows (download .zip from GitHub Releases)
# https://github.com/yvgude/lean-ctx/releases/latest
# Extract lean-ctx.exe and add to PATH

# All platforms via crates.io
cargo install lean-ctx</code></pre>

  <p>Then set up the shell hook and configure your editor:</p>
  <pre><code>lean-ctx init --global</code></pre>

  <p>
    See the <a href="/docs/installation">Installation guide</a> for editor-specific MCP configuration.
  </p>

  <h2>Verify It Works</h2>
  <p>
    Once configured, restart your editor and look for LeanCTX in the MCP tools list.
    You should see 21 tools including: <code>ctx_read</code>, <code>ctx_multi_read</code>, <code>ctx_tree</code>, <code>ctx_shell</code>,
    <code>ctx_search</code>, <code>ctx_compress</code>, <code>ctx_smart_read</code>, <code>ctx_delta</code>, <code>ctx_dedup</code>, <code>ctx_fill</code>,
    <code>ctx_intent</code>, <code>ctx_response</code>, <code>ctx_context</code>, <code>ctx_graph</code>, <code>ctx_discover</code>,
    <code>ctx_benchmark</code>, <code>ctx_metrics</code>, <code>ctx_analyze</code>, and <code>ctx_cache</code>.
  </p>

  <p>
    Use <code>ctx_benchmark</code> on a file to see per-strategy token savings, or run
    <code>lean-ctx benchmark run</code> on the CLI for a full project benchmark with preservation scores.
  </p>

